{
    "name": "david",
    "lang": "eng",
    "title": "David",
    "description": "A se­lec­tion of proverbs tak­en from the Book of Psalms in the Hebrew Bible",
    "sample-verse": "12:8",
    "books": [
        {
            "sections": [
                {
                    "paragraphs": [
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "2:11",
                                    "translation": "Serve Gᴏᴅ with fear and re­joice with trem­bling."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "4:4",
                                    "translation": "In your an­ger, do not sin. Pon­der in your heart on your bed and be still."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "4:5",
                                    "translation": "Of­fer the sacrifices of right­eous­ness and put your trust in Gᴏᴅ."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "12:8",
                                    "translation": "The wick­ed walk on eve­ry side when vile­ness is ex­alt­ed a­mong the chil­dren of men."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "15:1",
                                    "translation": "Gᴏᴅ, who may so­journ in your tent? Who may dwell on your ho­ly hill?"
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "15:2",
                                    "translation": "He who walks with in­teg­ri­ty and does what is right and speaks truth in his heart;"
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "15:3",
                                    "translation": "who does not slan­der with his tongue and does no evil to his neigh­bor and does not take up a re­proach against his friend;"
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "15:4",
                                    "translation": "who despises a vile per­son but hon­ors those who fear Gᴏᴅ; who keeps a prom­ise e­ven when it hurts and does not change;"
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "15:5",
                                    "translation": "who does not loan out his mon­ey with in­ter­est and does not take a bribe against the in­no­cent. He who does these things shall nev­er be moved."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "18:25",
                                    "translation": "Gᴏᴅ shows mer­cy to the mer­ci­ful."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "18:30",
                                    "translation": "The word of Gᴏᴅ proves true. He is a shield to all who take ref­uge in him."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "19:1",
                                    "translation": "The heavens de­clare the glo­ry of God and the skies show his hand­i­work."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "19:7",
                                    "translation": "The law of Gᴏᴅ is per­fect, re­viv­ing the soul. The tes­ti­mo­ny of Gᴏᴅ is trust­wor­thy, mak­ing wise the sim­ple."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "19:8",
                                    "translation": "The precepts of Gᴏᴅ are right, re­joic­ing the heart. The com­mand­ment of Gᴏᴅ is pure, enlightening the eyes."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "19:9",
                                    "translation": "The fear of Gᴏᴅ is clean, en­dur­ing for­ev­er. The laws of Gᴏᴅ are true and right­eous al­to­geth­er."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "27:14",
                                    "translation": "Wait for Gᴏᴅ. Be strong and let your heart take cour­age. Wait for Gᴏᴅ."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "30:5",
                                    "translation": "Weep­ing may last for a night, but joy co­mes in the morn­ing."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "32:10",
                                    "translation": "Man­y sorrows come to the wick­ed, but lov­ing-kind­ness surrounds him who trusts in Gᴏᴅ."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "33:6",
                                    "translation": "By the word of Gᴏᴅ the heavens were made and all their host by the breath of his mouth."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "34:13",
                                    "translation": "Keep your tongue from evil and your lips from speak­ing de­ceit."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "34:14",
                                    "translation": "De­part from evil and do good. Seek peace and pur­sue it."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "37:1",
                                    "translation": "Donʼt wor­ry a­bout evildoers, and donʼt en­vy wrongdoers."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "37:7",
                                    "translation": "Be still be­fore Gᴏᴅ and wait pa­tient­ly for him. Donʼt wor­ry a­bout him who prospers or a­bout him who carries out wick­ed schemes."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "37:8",
                                    "translation": "Cease from an­ger and for­sake wrath. Donʼt wor­ry: it on­ly leads to evil­do­ing."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "37:16",
                                    "translation": "A lit­tle that the right­eous has is bet­ter than the a­bun­dance of man­y wick­ed."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "37:21",
                                    "translation": "The wick­ed borrows and does not pay back, but the right­eous is gen­er­ous and gives."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "39:1",
                                    "translation": "I will guard my ways so that I may not sin with my tongue. I will muz­zle my mouth while the wick­ed are in my pres­ence."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "41:1",
                                    "translation": "Bless­ed is he who considers the poor. Gᴏᴅ will de­liv­er him in the day of trou­ble."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "46:1",
                                    "translation": "God is our ref­uge and strength, a ver­y pres­ent help in trou­ble."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "46:10",
                                    "translation": "Be still and know that I am God."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "49:16",
                                    "translation": "Do not be a­fraid when one is made rich, when the splen­dor of his house increases."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "49:17",
                                    "translation": "For when he dies he will car­ry noth­ing a­way. His glo­ry will not de­scend af­ter him."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "50:14",
                                    "translation": "Of­fer to God a sac­ri­fice of thanks­giv­ing, and pay your vows to the Most High,"
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "50:15",
                                    "translation": "and call on me in the day of trou­ble. I will de­liv­er you and you will glo­ri­fy me."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "55:22",
                                    "translation": "Cast your bur­den on Gᴏᴅ and he will sus­tain you. He will nev­er al­low the right­eous to be moved."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "82:3",
                                    "translation": "De­fend the poor and fa­ther­less. Do jus­tice to the afflicted and des­ti­tute."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "82:4",
                                    "translation": "Res­cue the poor and needy. De­liv­er them from the hand of the wick­ed."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "92:12",
                                    "translation": "The right­eous will flour­ish like the palm tree. He will grow like a ce­dar in Lebanon."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "96:2",
                                    "translation": "Sing to Gᴏᴅ, bless his name. Pro­claim his sal­va­tion from day to day."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "96:3",
                                    "translation": "De­clare his glo­ry a­mong the nations, his mar­vel­lous deeds a­mong all the peoples."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "100:1",
                                    "translation": "Make a joy­ful noise to Gᴏᴅ, all the earth."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "100:2",
                                    "translation": "Serve Gᴏᴅ with glad­ness. Come be­fore him with sing­ing."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "102:17",
                                    "translation": "Gᴏᴅ regards the pray­er of the des­ti­tute and does not de­spise their pray­er."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "103:8",
                                    "translation": "Gᴏᴅ is mer­ci­ful and gra­cious, slow to an­ger, abounding in lov­ing-kind­ness."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "105:1",
                                    "translation": "Give thanks to Gᴏᴅ. Call on his name. Make known his deeds a­mong the peoples."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "105:2",
                                    "translation": "Sing to him. Sing praises to him. Talk a­bout all his mar­vel­ous deeds."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "105:3",
                                    "translation": "Glo­ry in his ho­ly name. Let the hearts of those who seek Gᴏᴅ re­joice."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "105:4",
                                    "translation": "Seek Gᴏᴅ and his strength. Seek his face con­tin­u­al­ly."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "105:5",
                                    "translation": "Re­mem­ber the wonders that he has done, his miracles and the judgments he has pro­nounced."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "106:1",
                                    "translation": "Praise Gᴏᴅ. Give thanks to Gᴏᴅ, for he is good; for his lov­ing-kind­ness endures for­ev­er."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "111:10",
                                    "translation": "The fear of Gᴏᴅ is the be­gin­ning of wis­dom. Those who o­bey his commandments have good un­der­stand­ing."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "112:1",
                                    "translation": "Bless­ed is the man who fears Gᴏᴅ, who delights great­ly in his commandments."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "112:4",
                                    "translation": "For the up­right, light arises in the dark­ness. He is gra­cious, mer­ci­ful and right­eous."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "112:5",
                                    "translation": "It is well with the man who deals gen­er­ous­ly and lends, who conducts his af­fairs with jus­tice."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "118:8",
                                    "translation": "It is bet­ter to take ref­uge in Gᴏᴅ than to put con­fi­dence in man."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "118:9",
                                    "translation": "It is bet­ter to take ref­uge in Gᴏᴅ than to put con­fi­dence in prin­ces."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "122:6",
                                    "translation": "Pray for the peace of Je­ru­sa­lem."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "127:1",
                                    "translation": "Ex­cept Gᴏᴅ build the house, they la­bor in vain who build it. Ex­cept Gᴏᴅ keep the cit­y, the watch­man stays a­wake in vain."
                                },
                                {
                                    "ref": "127:2",
                                    "translation": "It is vain for you to rise up ear­ly, to stay up late, to eat the bread of toil—for he gives sleep to his be­lov­ed."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "127:3",
                                    "translation": "Chil­dren are a her­it­age from Gᴏᴅ and the fruit of the womb is a re­ward."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "133:1",
                                    "translation": "How good and pleas­ant it is for brothers to live to­geth­er in u­ni­ty."
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "verses": [
                                {
                                    "ref": "146:3",
                                    "translation": "Do not put your trust in prin­ces or in the son of man, who can­not save."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
